==Introduction==

The '''Reports''' widget displays the links to the reports, generated by the Reports Generator, which are related to the data entity currently displayed on the page.


==Definition==
;Report Categories Definition

First, the Categories of the reports needs to be defined. Report categories allows to classify the reports primarily based on their goals and the target audience.

<pre>
<WikiModel>

  <DataModel>
  </DataModel>

  <ReportsModel>
    <categories>
      <category name="{REPORT CATEGORY NAME}">{REPORT CATEGORY DESCRIPTION}</category>
      ...
    </categories>
  </ReportsModel

</WikiModel>
</pre>

{| class="helptable"
|-
! {REPORT CATEGORY NAME}
| A name of the report category
|-
! {REPORT CATEGORY DESCRIPTION}
| A description of the report category.
|}


;Reports Definition

Secondly, the reports being generated by the [[Help:Reports Generator|Reports Generator]] needs to be specified in the context of the DataModel elements for which they are generated.

The reports might be specified on various levels, depending on the scope of the report:
* '''Data Model-level''', for reports covering most of the information within the Model
* '''Package-level''', for reports covering most of the Concepts within single Package
* '''Concept-level''', for reports addressing primarily the scope of single Concept (or even single instance of the Concept)

<pre>
<DataModel>
  <concepts>
    <package name="{PACKAGE NAME}">

      <concept name="{CONCEPT NAME}">
        <structure>
        </structure>
        <reports>                                  <!-- Concept level reports -->
          <report name="{REPORT NAME}" scope="{REPORT SCOPE}" category="{REPORT CATEGORY NAME}" file="{REPORT FILE NAME}"/>
          ..
        </reports>
      </concept>

      <reports>                                    <!-- Package level reports -->
        <report name="{REPORT NAME}" scope="{REPORT SCOPE}" category="{REPORT CATEGORY NAME}" file="{REPORT FILE NAME}"/>
        ..
      </reports>

    </package>
    ...
  </concepts>

  <reports>                                        <!-- Data Model level reports -->
    <report name="{REPORT NAME}" scope="{REPORT SCOPE}" category="{REPORT CATEGORY NAME}" file="{REPORT FILE NAME}"/>
    ..
  </reports>
</DataModelModel>
</pre>

{| class="helptable"
|-
! {REPORT CATEGORY NAME}
| A name of the report category. The name must exists in the <nowiki><categories></nowiki> section
|-
! {REPORT NAME}
| A name of the report
|-
! {REPORT SCOPE}
| A scope of the report. Allowed values:
* '''package'''. The report addresses all data entities for given Package.
* '''concept'''. The report addresses all data entities for given Concept.
* '''instance]'''. The report addresses specific data entity/instance displayed on the page.
|-
! {REPORT FILE NAME}
| A name of the file which is being generated. For the reports generated for particular instance, the @INSTANCE variable might be used in the file name string. This variable is replaced with the current page name when the page is rendered.
|}


==Example==
<pre>
<DataModel>

  <concepts>

    <package name="Event Management">
      <concept name="Event">
        <structure>
        </structure>
        <reports>
          <report name="Event Test Planning" scope="instance" category="Testing" file="@INSTANCE Test Planning Perspective.pdf"/>
          <report name="Event Test Results"  scope="instance" category="Testing" file="@INSTANCE Test Results Perspective.pdf"/>
        </reports>
      </concept>

      <concept name="Capability Configuration">
        <structure>
          <property name="Is tested during" refersTo="Event"/>
        </structure>
        <reports>
          <report name="Capability Test Planning" scope="instance" category="Testing" file="@INSTANCE Test Planning Perspective.pdf"/>
          <report name="Capability Test Results"  scope="instance" category="Testing" file="@INSTANCE Test Results Perspective.pdf"/>
        </reports>
      </concept>

      <concept name="Test Case">
        <structure layout="sections">
          <property name="Is tested during" refersTo="Event"/>
          <property name="Is performed by" refersTo="Capability Configuration"/>
        </structure>
      </concept>

      <reports>
        <report name="Events Summary" scope="package" category="Testing" file="Events Summary.pdf"/>
      </reports>
    </package>

   </concepts>
</DataModel>

<ReportsModel>
  <categories>
    <category name="Testing">
      Perspectives providing a comprehensive view of the testing performed at various testing Events.
    </category>
  </categories>
</ReportsModel>

</pre>

In the example above several reports are being generated:
* two different types of reports for each Event instance (Event Test Planning, Event Test Results)
* two different types of reports for each Capability Configuration participating ion the Event (Capability Test Planning, Capability Test Results)
* one report with the summary of all testing across all Events (Events Summary)


